ENTRY            K2777   20260503   20260508   20260508       K024
SUBENT        K2777001   20260503   20260508   20260508       K024
BIB                 11         22
TITLE      Experimental study of photoneutron spectra from
           tantalum, tungsten, and bismuth targets for 16.6 MeV
           polarized photons
AUTHOR     (T.H.T.Nguyen, T.Sanami, H.Yamazaki, T.Itoga,
            Y.Kirihara, K.Sugihara, T.K.Tuyet, M.F.B.M.Zin,
            S.Miyamoto, S.Hashimoto, Y.Asano)
INSTITUTE  (2JPNSOK,2JPNKEK,2JPNJSR,2JPNJAE,2JPNOSA,2JPNHIT)
REFERENCE  (J,NST,61,261,2024)
INC-SOURCE (LCS)
SAMPLE     - Chemical-form of target is element.
           - Physical-form of target is solid.
METHOD     (TOF)
           (PSD) to separate the neutrons from gamma rays
FACILITY   (SRING,2JPNHIT) NewSUBARU
DETECTOR   (SCIN) Organic liquid scintillators (NE213)
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-T) Total uncertainty
           (ERR-1) Number of photons
           (ERR-2) Detection efficiency
           (ERR-3) Solid angle
           (ERR-S,4.,15.) neutron counting (4-15%)
HISTORY    (20240703C) Y. O
           (20250730R) Received by e-mail from Dr. T. Nguyen.
ENDBIB              22
COMMON               4          3
EN         ERR-1      ERR-2      ERR-3
MEV        PER-CENT   PER-CENT   PER-CENT
 16.6       5.         5.         0.2
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           29
